The paper deals with the task of font size detection in compressed text documents, which is a subfield of document image analysis and OCRing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the processing and analysis of text documents. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for font size detection, which falls under the categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.DL (Deep Learning), and cs.CL (Computational Linguistics). Additionally, the use of features such as line height and ascender height for font size detection suggests the involvement of statistical modeling and regression analysis, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
